By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) â€“ The Supreme Court on Monday confirmed Ahmad Fintiri of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) as the winner of the Adamawa governorship election held in the state. Shortly after the affirmation of Samuel Ortom as Benue Governor, the apex court ruled that Ahmad Fintiri won the Adamawa election contrary to the claims of his arch-rival, Jibrilla Bindow of the All Progressives Congress (APC). He court ruled that Bindow had failed to prove his allegation of the rigging of the election in favour of Fintiri.